line_1: Strange Terror of Mankind! By thee misled,
line_2: Not Conscience, Quicksands, Rocks, or Death they dread!

line_1: But, if by vain self-love misled,
line_2: And think, by weak illusions fed,

line_1: In ign'rance train'd, by prejudice misled;
line_2: Poor abject souls in superstition bred,

line_1: By guileful Hope misled:
line_2: Ambition loves to tread;

line_1: False glory hath my youth mis-led,
line_2: The case is plain, the Monarch said;

line_1: By self-distrust misled.
line_2: And fearful shews its head;

line_1: By passion blinded, by despair misled,
line_2: I walk'd in clouds. — She is already dead!

line_1: No passion's mists, by no false joys misled,
line_2: No ties forgot, no duties left unpaid,

line_1: No passion's mists, by no false joys misled,
line_2: No lays unfinish'd, and no aching head.

line_1: No more by vain prosperity misled,
line_2: With resignation bow'd his hoary head,

line_1: What Now should tempt us, by false hopes misled,
line_2: Learning's unfashionable paths to tread;

line_1: By freely drinking many are misled;
line_2: By Wine the strongest have been conquered:

line_1: How oft have wretched Mortals been misled,
line_2: With murd'rous Hands their Rival's Blood to shed?

line_1: If by the day's illusive scenes misled,
line_2: My erring soul from Virtue's path has stray'd:

line_1: TOO long by some fatality misled,
line_2: From pride resulting, or from folly bred;

line_1: Thy erring fire, by this misled,
line_2: Shall scatter pleasures round thy head,

line_1: But lest, by frail desires misled,
line_2: The girls forbidden paths should tread,

line_1: "In wild confusion; through free will misled,
line_2: "The whole creation shrivels to a shade. —

line_1: "In wild confusion; through free will misled,
line_2: "And tempted to go wrong from punishment delay'd."

line_1: By this the Sophists were of old misled:
line_2: See what a monstrous race from one mistake is bred!

line_1: More are by weakness than by vice misled —
line_2: Yet, of the numbers who in error tread,

line_1: Or is thy judgment by thy heart misled
line_2: By these fair flattering words, she rais'd her head;

line_1: Or is thy judgment by thy heart misled
line_2: Mock'st thou my sorrows, Fairy Son? she said.
